@startuml
' @id(SEQ-CANVAS-FISHEYE)
' @ref(USE-FISHEYE-FOCUS)
' @desc(SEQ-CANVAS-FISHEYE, "Per-frame canvas flow: base scale from scroll zoom + drag pan, then a center-fixed fisheye remap of the rendered texture before it is painted; no toolbar zoom buttons exist.")
' Objective-side flow for the focus+context canvas. The fisheye is a
' display-time remap applied after the base zoom/pan placement.
title Focus a diagram region with the center fisheye (objective)

actor "Developer" as Dev
participant "MddViewer\n(eframe::App)" as Viewer
participant "CanvasView\n(zoom, pan, fisheye)" as CV
participant "Diagram texture\n(rendered SVG)" as Tex
participant "egui painter" as Painter

Dev -> Viewer : scroll wheel over canvas
Viewer -> CV : adjust base zoom at cursor
Dev -> Viewer : drag canvas
Viewer -> CV : pan += drag_delta
note right of CV
  No Reset / Zoom + / Zoom - buttons exist.
  Zoom is scroll-only; pan is drag-only.
  Focal point is FIXED at the canvas centre
  (see OCL-FISHEYE-FOCAL-CENTER).
end note

loop each painted frame
  Viewer -> CV : focal = canvas_rect.center()
  Viewer -> Tex : sample base-placed texture (zoom * pan)
  Viewer -> CV : fisheye_remap(point, focal, strength, radius)
  note right of Viewer
    Radial remap around the centre: distance d from
    focal is warped so small d magnifies (bulge) and
    large d compresses toward the edges. Strength is
    bounded; at strength 0 the canvas is the plain
    base placement.
  end note
  Viewer -> Painter : paint warped mesh / image with focal magnified
  Painter --> Dev : centre bulges, edges curve away
end
@enduml
